18.303 | Linear Partial Differential Equations: Analysis and Numerics | http://ocw.mit.edu/courses/mathematics/18-303-linear-partial-differential-equations-analysis-and-numerics-fall-2014 | level:Undergraduate instructors:Steven G. Johnson term:Fall 2014 features:Assignments and solutions, Exams and solutions description:This course provides students with the basic analytical and computational tools of linear partial differential equations (PDEs) for practical applications in science engineering, including heat / diffusion, wave, and Poisson equations. Analytics emphasize the viewpoint of linear algebra and the analogy with finite matrix problems. Numerics focus on finite-difference and finite-element techniques to reduce PDEs to matrix problems. The Julia Language (a free, open-source environment) is introduced and used in homework for simple examples.
